7t8.title: Meta-utility function
7t8.clickbait: Preference frameworks built out of simple utility functions, but where, e.g., the 'correct' utility function for a possible world depends on whether a button is pressed.
7t8.text: A "meta-utility function" is a [5f preference framework] built by composing multiple simple [1fw utility functions] into a more complicated structure.  The point might be, e.g., to describe an [-agent] that [1b7 optimizes different utility functions depending on whether a switch is pressed], or an agent that [7s2 learns a 'correct' utility function] by observing data informative about some [-7s6].  For central examples see [1b7] and [7s2].
